datasets.name: 6cee62b2
queryLines:
SELECT ship, homeport, lat, long,
    CASE 
        WHEN MAX(CASE WHEN operable = 'false' THEN 1 ELSE 0 END) >= 1 THEN 'red'
        WHEN COUNT(fault) >= 1 THEN 'yellow'
        ELSE 'green'
    END AS status 
FROM ahahn_demo.dbdemos_navy_pdm.ship_current_status_gold
GROUP BY ALL;

datasets.name: 4bf52947
queryLines:
SELECT COUNT(*) num_faults, p.type FROM ahahn_demo.dbdemos_navy_pdm.ship_current_status_gold AS s
LEFT JOIN ahahn_demo.dbdemos_navy_pdm.parts p
ON find_in_set(s.prediction, array_join(p.sensors, ',')) > 0
WHERE prediction != 'ok' AND type IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY ALL

datasets.name: 66f9103e
queryLines:
WITH s AS (
    SELECT prediction, homeport, COUNT(*) num_faults
    FROM ahahn_demo.dbdemos_navy_pdm.ship_current_status_gold
    GROUP BY prediction, homeport
), 
p AS (
    SELECT stock_location flc, parts.type part, stock_available stock, 
            CASE 
                WHEN stock_location = 'FLC Norfolk' THEN 'NB Norfolk'
                WHEN stock_location = 'FLC Jacksonville' THEN 'NS Mayport'
                WHEN stock_location = 'FLC San Diego' THEN 'NB San Diego'
                WHEN stock_location = 'FLC Pearl Harbor' THEN 'NS Pearl Harbor'
                WHEN stock_location = 'FLC Puget Sound' THEN 'NB San Diego'
            END nearest_homeport
            , sensor  -- Include a new column to store the exploded sensor value
    FROM ahahn_demo.dbdemos_navy_pdm.parts
    LATERAL VIEW explode(sensors) p_ex AS sensor
)

SELECT p.flc, p.part, p.stock, s.homeport hpt_demand, (s.num_faults - p.stock) AS deficit
FROM s
LEFT JOIN p ON s.prediction = p.sensor AND p.nearest_homeport = s.homeport
WHERE (s.num_faults - p.stock) > 0 AND (s.num_faults - p.stock) IS NOT NULL;

queryLines:
SELECT 
  homeport, 
  CAST(lat AS DOUBLE) AS lat, 
  CAST(long AS DOUBLE) AS long, 
  model, 
  ship, 
  turbine_id, 
  _rescued_data 
FROM ahahn_demo.dbdemos_navy_pdm.ship_meta

datasets.name: f0a18247
queryLines:
WITH srn AS (
  SELECT 
    REPLACE(ship, '_', ' ') AS ship, 
    type, 
    stock_location, 
    qty_shipped 
  FROM 
    ahahn_demo.dbdemos_navy_pdm.shipment_recommendations_navy
)
SELECT 
  srn.*, 
  sm.homeport 
FROM 
  srn
JOIN 
  ahahn_demo.dbdemos_navy_pdm.ship_meta AS sm 
ON 
  sm.ship LIKE CONCAT('%', srn.ship, '%')
WHERE srn.qty_shipped > 0

# Parts Management + Supply Chain Optimization 

Based on our Predictive maintenance model and our stock status, we are able to provide recommendation to better organize our stock and potentially adjust spare parts command.  

The potential use-cases and potential revenue optimizations are huge. As other example we can also run analysis on the faulty equipment history and potentially detect frequent issues to take preventive action on the hardware.
